reviewText:
Alright! Time for another review.
So I've been playing Blades of Time, and as an Hack'n'Slash lover, this game surprised me.

This is a very addictive game, not because of its story, or voice acting, its puzzles, or anything in particular, but when you start playing it just keeps you glued to it, for short to medium periods of time, but you always need to come back for more. This is only until you finish the main storyline.

So, what does the game do well and not so well? Here's a list for you:

Pros:
Fun fighting, quick and rather easy to pulloff combos* (see in Cons);
Weapons (such as rifles and cannons) for long range engagements;
Very distinct areas, a wide variety of sights to amuse yourself and fight your way through;
Decent and somewhat interesting bossfights;
Hidden chests and rewards spread all over the world as you go through the levels, be on the lookout for those as they hold new equipment* (see in Cons)
Rather interesting main character (Ayumi), as time goes on you start to develop more interest in her intentions and motivation to go on.
Cons:
Not the best special abilities, since they're all the same, but with different side effects (burning, or freezing your enemies, etc.)
Some frustrating fights (arenas and/or mini boss fights);
Not the best graphical fidelity, but has its good moments;
A lot of the enemy characters look the same and dress the same;
Weak voice acting, at least in English tongue (in Japanese seems to be better)
The rewards you get from hidden chests or bossfights, only have a different stat (e.g. you can have a pair of swords that Increases fire damage and another pair that has a different model but instead gives you Freezes enemies for a longer period), the same goes for rings, amulets, but it's slightly more in-depth when it comes to weapons though;
Some of the puzzles might be frustrating to finish and some you might even have to take a wild guess in order to proceed to the next area, as sometimes you have no clue or explanation on what to do.

Extras:

Despite the longer Cons list, I really enjoyed this game.
I didn't mention the storyline above, because it's up to you to love it or hate it. I didn't find it amazing, but it's not bad either if you like the gameplay, you'll go along with the story too. Also, the storyline might last you around 8 hours depending on how many secrets you find and the difficulty you play on.
The puzzles are decent, and there are a few of them here and there. Not great, not bad, some are quick and some are frustrating.
The multiplayer looks interesting, but it's not working (or at least there isn't anyone playing). It's a shame truthfully, looks really fun and somewhat innovative imho.


If you happen to catch this game on sale or in a bundle, grab it if you can!
And that's it, if you like Hack'n'Slash games, you'll like this one, it's no Devil May Cry, but it's decent enough to give it a go. After all, you're playing this to kill everything around you, right?

This game is quite good, and certainly not so bad as the Critic says.

The best things are:
- very good animations and combat skills;
- wonderful environments;
- Ayumi, a beautiful, sexy and quite crazy girl;
- Boss fights and bestiary.

The bad things are:
- plot: quite banal;
- the DLC Dismal Swamp": really awful

